    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and grate <strong>half</strong> your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Slice the<strong> remaining onion </strong>finely</p><p>Slice your <strong>white cup</strong> <strong>mushrooms</strong></p><p>Slice <strong>half</strong> your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> into rounds and finely dice the <strong>remaining red chilli</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-meatball-and-mushroom-pho/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>grated onion</strong>, <strong>diced chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and<strong> mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Divide the <strong>meatball mixture</strong> and shape them into 4 meatballs per person</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-meatball-and-mushroom-pho/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min on each side or until browned</p><p>Once the <strong>meatballs</strong> have browned, transfer them to a plate and set aside, these will finish cooking in the sauce later (reserve the pan!)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-meatball-and-mushroom-pho/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>rice noodles</strong> to a pot and cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> until fully submerged</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender, then drain</p><p>Once drained, return the <strong>noodles</strong> to the pot and set aside</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-meatball-and-mushroom-pho/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat, with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and <strong>sliced mushrooms </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>pho broth paste</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>and <strong>soy sauce </strong>with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml]<strong> </strong></span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-meatball-and-mushroom-pho/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>browned meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook, covered for 12-15 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Once cooked through, add the <strong>drained noodles </strong>to the pan and cook for 1 min or until warmed through \u2013 this is your <strong>meatball & mushroom pho</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-meatball-and-mushroom-pho/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-meatball-and-mushroom-pho/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>meatball & mushroom pho</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> sliced spring onion</strong>, <strong>chilli rounds </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)<strong> </strong>and <strong>chopped mint & coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
